    <text>
        <body>
            
            <div1 type="letter">
                
                <pb facs="nei.j4a.21.9-11_0001"/>
                
                <note type="curatorial">Missouri Collection</note>
                <fw type="curatorial">9</fw>
                
                <opener>
                    <dateline>
                        502 <hi rend="caps">S.</hi> State St.
                        Springfield Illinois
                        Sept. 10, 1944
                    </dateline>
                  
                    <address>
                        <addrLine>Jno <hi rend="caps">G</hi> Neihardt</addrLine>
                
                        <addrLine>2300 So Michigan</addrLine>
                    </address>
                    
                    <salute>Dear Mr. Neihardt:</salute>
                </opener>
                <p>It is such a relief to get a letter that does not scold or rebuke me for feeling despair when one knows the administer really never has experienced    
                
                <pb facs="nei.j4a.21.9-11_0002"/>
                
                    <fw type="curatorial">10</fw>
                    
                    anything deeply enough to suffer an endless agony.</p>
                
                <p>Yes I belong to Episcopalian church but I have not gone for twelve years except once this summer. I consider frequently finding strength there but abandon the idea.</p>
                
                <p>Meditation is the nearest avenue to prayer I know, it is the loss of contact with any will to be or do, any spring of power that upsets, I should not quite say frightens me. The solution if I find it will
                
                <pb facs="nei.j4a.21.9-11_0003"/>
                    
                    <fw type="curatorial">11</fw>
                
                    have to be very simple. Not knowing Black Elk's prayer I am curious, hopeful, willing to lean on anything that will pull me out of this dying-living state.</p>
                
                <p>Nothing seems silly that is sensitized. If you are willing to write of the Prayer I'll appreciate any message you care to send on.</p>
                <closer>
                    <salute>Gratefully yours,</salute>
                    <signed>Elizabeth Graham</signed>
                </closer>        
                
            </div1>
        </body>
        
